      <p class="text-slate-500 mb-10">Avant de coder sérieusement, il te faut un filet de sécurité. Git et GitHub te permettent de ne jamais perdre ton travail — et de revenir en arrière si quelque chose se casse.</p>

      <!-- Git vs GitHub -->
      <div class="card p-7 mb-5">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5 mb-5">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-600 to-red-700 flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-3xl">🌿</div>
          <div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-1">
              <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold">Git &amp; GitHub</h3>
              <span class="tag bg-orange-500/15 text-orange-300 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-md px-2 py-0.5">Versioning</span>
              <span class="maturity-badge badge-start">Démarrage</span>
              <span class="tag bg-slate-700/40 text-slate-400 border border-slate-600/20 rounded-md px-2 py-0.5">Gratuit</span>
            </div>
